training_organizations.name: Indiana DCS Staff Training
training_organizations.description: The Indiana Department of Child Services provides training for all new family case managers and ongoing courses through its Staff Development division. Training ensures workers understand Indiana’s structured decision-making processes, legal requirements, and engage in skill-building (like conducting assessments, testifying in court) to effectively serve children and families.

training_organizations.name: The Villages of Indiana
training_organizations.description: A nonprofit child and family services agency that partners with Indiana DCS to support foster care and adoption. The Villages recruits and trains foster parents, provides therapeutic foster care for children with special needs, and offers family services (like kinship care support and reunification programs) to augment DCS’ capacity in caring for children.

training_organizations.name: Eckerd Connects (Rapid Safety Feedback)
training_organizations.description: Indiana DCS worked with Eckerd Connects to implement a “Rapid Safety Feedback” predictive analytics tool that helped flag high-risk cases for review:contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}. Through this initiative, Eckerd provided analytic services and training to Indiana supervisors on using data to intervene earlier in potentially dangerous cases (this was a pilot effort to prevent child fatalities).

policies.TribalFoster: Yes, Tribes within state provide foster care
policies.FatalitiesReview: Yes, reviews are required for all or some cases
policies.EquityStaff_Specify: Indiana's Department of Child Services hired and put in place a Strategic Equity Officer in 2022
policies.Exempt_OtherSpecify: Inadequate food, or signs of malnutrition and considered a type of neglect but fasting for religious reason is excluded
policies.NearFatalitiesReview: Yes, reviews can be conducted but are not required
policies.TribalFoster_Specify: The Pokagon Band of Potawatomi Indians
policies.InvestReq_OtherSpecify: Notify the parent, guardian, or custodian of the allegation; Provide child's caregiver and alleged perpetrator copy of the report; Review safety assessment with supervisor; Activate the AlertMedia app prior to face-to-face interactions with clients and utilize the AlertMedia app throughout each interaction; Ask the parent, guardian, or custodian to sign the Release for Use of Photographs form, and if the signature is obtained, take photographs of all children in the home.
policies.ScreenInfo_OtherSpecify: Whether the alleged child abuse and/or neglect occurred within the state of Indiana, and if so, whether there is any current risk of harm to the child in Indiana.
policies.DefAge_VaryByTypeSpecify: For certain acts of sexual abuse, the child's age can vary between age 14 to under age 18
policies.EquityStaff_OtherSpecify: Indiana's Department of Child Services Strategic Equity Officer works with all child welfare agencies within Indiana to analyze success and areas of opportunity for equity and inclusion to child welfare and probation youth cases
policies.DefHarm_VaryByTypeSpecify: For neglect, emotional maltreatment, or physical abuse, the extent of harm is both physical and mental condition; For abandonment, the extent of harm is harmful environment/conditions
policies.DefPerp_VaryByTypeSpecify: For sexual abuse, there is no requirement for the perpetrator to be the child's parent, guardian, or custodian, which is required for all other types of maltreatment
policies.AntiDiscrim_Who_SomeSpecify: Children and youth in foster care
policies.AntiDiscrim_Who_VarySpecify: Children and youth in foster care are covered for sex, familial status, and financial situation; All children, youth, and families engaged in the child welfare system are covered for the following characteristics: age, race, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, disability, religion, national origin, marital status, color, and political beliefs or affiliations
policies.InvestQual_ExperienceSpecify: A Bachelor's degree can be supplemented by either: (1) An Associate degree with a minimum of two years of human services job experience; (2) Completion of 30 college credit hours from an accredited institution with a minimum of four years of human services job experience; or (3) A minimum of at least five years of human services job experience
policies.AntiDiscrim_Apply_SomeSpecify: When engaging with all children in foster care
policies.AntiDiscrim_Apply_VarySpecify: Sex, familial status, and financial situation apply when engaging with all children in foster care; The following characteristics apply broadly to all decision points or parts of the child welfare system: age, race, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, disability, religion, national origin, marital status, color, and political beliefs or affiliations
policies.AntiDiscrim_Staff_VarySpecify: (1) Age, race, sexual orientation, disability, religion, national origin, marital status, color, and political beliefs or affiliations for staff from child welfare agency that work directly with children, youth, and families; (2) Gender identity or expression, sex, familial status, and financial situation are specified for all child welfare agency employees, including those that don't work directly with children, youth, and families
policies.InvestReq_MHEvalCases_Specify: (1) The child's Child and Adolescent Needs and Strengths (CANS) Assessment indicates a need for a full mental health assessment; (2) The child exhibits behaviors that would cause a reasonable person to believe he or she is a danger to him or herself and/or others
policies.AntiDiscrim_Staff_OtherSpecify: All DCS employees, including those that don't work directly with children, youth, and families
policies.CaseManagerQual_ExperienceSpec: A Bachelor's degree can be supplemented by either: (1) An Associate degree with a minimum of two years of human services job experience; (2) Completion of 30 college credit hours from an accredited institution with a minimum of four years of human services job experience; or (3) A minimum of at least five years of human services job experience
policies.InvestReq_MedEvalCases_Specify: Physical abuse; Sexual abuse; Child has been removed from a home with a contaminating controlled substance; Child is under 2 years old and shaking or a head injury is alleged
policies.ScreenerQual_ExperienceSpecify: A Bachelor's degree can be supplemented by either: (1) An Associate degree with a minimum of two years of human services job experience; (2) Completion of 30 college credit hours from an accredited institution with a minimum of four years of human services job experience; or (3) A minimum of at least five years of human services job experience
policies.InvestReq_HomeStudyCases_Specify: Alleged incident occurred at home or there are concerns about the condition of the home
policies.InvestReq_HomeVisitCases_Specify: Alleged incident occurred at home or there are concerns about the condition of the home
policies.InvestReq_PerpInterviewCase_Spec: Required unless an attorney representing the alleged perpetrator informs the Department of Child Services (DCS) that their client will not participate; The alleged perpetrator's identity is unknown or they cannot be found; The alleged perpetrator is a child and their parent, guardian, or custodian does not consent; The alleged perpetrator has already been interviewed by law enforcement and DCS can get a copy of the report and a transcript or recording
